Autonomation - Intelligent Automation - Jidoka

  * Automate a process and make the machines alert when there are problems.
  * One person can monitor multiple processes and stop the production line when a problem occurs.
  * Multiple people work to solve the problem before resuming the line.
  * Stop when there is a quality problem.
%
Mistake Proofing - Poka Yoke

Avoid defects using simple mechanisms and practices:
  * enabling the system to prevent mistakes.
  * raising an alarm when a mistake is made.

Three golden rules of Mistake Proofing:
  * Don't accept a defect/mistake from a supplier.
  * Don't make a defect.
  * Don't pass on a defect to a customer.

Practices for Mistake Proofing:
  * checklist based on past defectsx which can re-occur.
  * automated tests that will run the moment a build is made/compiled.
%
Visual controls

The central idea is to make the status of an activity or process visible.

  * Present the current status of production schedule quality and problem to be made visible.
  * Easy to see, understand and respond to.
%
Go See Yourself - Genchi Gengutsu

  * Helps decision makers to have first hand and reliable information.
  * Calls for direct observation of the situation.
  * Know work environment, interact with team members, and use the learning to provide solutions for operational excellence.
%
Five Whys for Root Cause Analysis

Problem -> Why -> Why -> Why -> Why -> Why -> Root cause

In most cases the root cause can be found by asking up to five rounds of Why.
In come cases one may find multiple causes, keep tracing each branch until you get to the root of each.
